<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/950</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of the Chief of the Division of
                                    Latin-American Affairs of the Department of State</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_SJH2"><hi rend="italic">Stabler</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-19">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Colombian Minister telephoned the Latin-American Division this
                                morning and informed Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SJH2">Stabler</persName> that a cablegram had been received by the
                                Minister which stated that the Government of Colombia had replied to
                                the invitation of the Argentine Government to be present at the
                                conference of American nations, saying that it would be unable to
                                attend.</p>
                            <pb facs="0543" n="371" xml:id="pg_371"/>
                            <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_UCA1">Urueta</persName> requested that this
                                information be conveyed to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName> as of possible interest to him.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>